messages.messageBody:
PSoroosh@... wrote:
>
> What does "Num Lock" do? (on the computer keyboard)
>

It makes the set of keys that are to the right most side of
my keyboard into something resembling an adding machine keypad.
Instead of the key being "Home" it's 7, instead of up arrow it's
8, etc. I use it a lot when I use Quicken or a spreadsheet.

--

Cindy Ferguson
crma@...

messages.msgSnippet: My Num Lock is on the 10-key portion of the keyboard and when pushed, allows me to use the numbers on those keys instead of what is written on the bottom of
messages.messageBody:
My Num Lock is on the 10-key portion of the keyboard and when pushed,
allows me to use the numbers on those keys instead of what is written on
the bottom of each numbered key: Home or End, PgUp, arrows, etc. Hope
that is clear
Carolyn
